# Axiom Claude Guidelines

This project follows Axiom conventions.

## App Actions

- Organize business logic into small reusable actions in `app/Actions`.
- Name actions by what they do and keep a single public `handle()` method.
- Inject dependencies through constructor promoted properties.
- Use `php artisan make:action "{name}" --no-interaction` for new actions.
- Wrap multi-model writes in `DB::transaction()` when needed.

## Architecture

- Prefer DTOs over loose arrays at boundaries.
- Keep controllers thin and push business logic into actions.
- Follow the existing project structure and naming conventions.
- Reuse existing components before adding new ones.

## PHP And Quality

- Use `declare(strict_types=1);`.
- Keep classes `final` unless extension is intentional.
- Prefer `readonly` objects and explicit typing throughout.
- Use curly braces for control structures.
- Avoid unnecessary PHPDoc and inline comments.
- Prefer static-analysis-friendly code over clever shortcuts.
- Do not leave `dd`, `dump`, or `ray` in committed code.

## Testing

- Add or update tests whenever behavior changes.

## Skills

- When present, follow the focused workflow docs in `.ai/skills/`.
